name: .SKF File Extension
summary: Learn about .SKF files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: An SKF file is a CAD drawing created by AutoSketch, a CAD program used for creating 2D conceptual sketches and other technical drawings. SKF files can only be created and opened by AutoSketch, but can be converted to the .DWG format in the software.

content: The SKF file is the main format used by AutoSketch to save drawings. However, the program also supports the SKD, .DWG, and .DXF formats.
NOTE: AutoSketch was discontinued after the release of version 10 in November 2008.
